A jet of flames erupted from Thassalin's jaws as the colossal Thraki burned a specific patch of the forest, then circled above, observing it for a moment. Oddly, as it had slowed down, the strange sounds of cries behind it had stopped. Thassalin had forgotten he had passengers on his back.
"Come on, Tenuk, you've already turned into a Thraki before!"
"My flight is very different. I don't let myself be roughly lifted by a huge pink dragon!"
"Isn't it not so unpleasant, Kayel?"
Kayel was clearly not in agreement with Nyssi; he seemed less black than usual and had planted his claws into Thassalin's back, to the point that he had made the Thraki bleed, but obviously, he didn't care much. That said, Thassalin had realized he had terrified his new friends and found a clearing to land.
"MY APOLOGIES, I SMELLED A SWEET SMELL. I HAD TO CHECK."
"You had to drag us here with you?" Tenuk said as he slid down Thassalin's back along his tail. "And we left Retvik behind! We abandoned our strong and great warrior! How will he catch up with us?"
"He will find a way," retorted Nissy. "Retvik is slow, but not stupid."
"Okay, but does Retvik know how to drive?"
Nissy blinked and turned back to Tenuk. "Of course he knows how to drive."
"Have you ever seen Retvik driving a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like you, and I've never seen him drive anything like Kayel's little cute car either, and if he started coming to work by car, it's only because YOU drove us there. He just has this bike."
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Thassalin suddenly burst into laughter and no one understood what was making him laugh. It took him far too long to regain his composure.
"I'm sorry, but I was imagining your big friend in armor on a tiny bike meant for little Temthan children. It was so funny! I would have loved to be able to read minds. It's a precious thought! ONE I CANNOT SHARE!"
Kayel chuckled, imagining what Thassalin was thinking. "Yes, that's right. But what did you pick up and why did you fly off so quickly?"
Thassalin growled, took off, and disappeared briefly before returning and dropping a carcass in front of Nyssi. It was an Orothrack, a rare golden and white dragon-like creature. But it was missing its head. "ANOTHER DEATH. I HEAR THEIR CRIES. I FEEL THEIR BLOOD. I AM PROGRAMMED TO PROTECT AND HUNT. AS YISINI DEMANDS. THE CREATURES ARE CLOSE."
The powerful Thraki suddenly froze. Nyssi and Kayel also, their attention drawn by a clearing in the glade. Something big and black was staring at them, whistling. Whatever it was, this creature opened two massive pairs of wings and dove straight at Thassalin, without caring about the three smaller beings on its way. Kayel and Tenuk managed to take cover just in time, but Nyssi ended up being dragged and almost thrown onto Thassalin.
Thassalin reacted to the aggression by grabbing Nyssi and throwing her onto his back, using his tail's length and dexterity to do so, before taking off. The two-winged black creature quickly rushed after them.
Kayel blew on the rifle he had on his back, then opened a pouch in which there was a belt of ammunition. He put it across his body to have easy access to it, but quickly realized that Nyssi, the Thraki, and the monster were no longer visible.
"Hey Tenuk, how about you turn into something that flies?" asked Kayel.
"You want to chase them?"
"Yes, of course!"
"But... one of them is a giant monster!"
"And what of it? I have an ultra powerful rifle in my hands right now, ready to use. I just need to see it to shoot it."
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to make some space. With a weak, slightly pained growl, his body expanded, his fur was replaced by scales, and his arms transformed into wings. He quickly reverted back to his normal light blue Thraki form, but his eyes remained red.
"Get on."
Having regained a more normal appearance as a Thraki, Tenuk now had his back covered in scales, but a pair of spikes had also grown on top, useful for Kayel to grip. Tenuk needed a little time to take off, but once in the air, he quickly oriented himself and attempted a pursuit.
However, Tenuk and Kayel quickly realized they weren't alone. A second dark creature emerged from below, and Tenuk barely managed to avoid it.
I suppose it's the other big scary monster that was troubling Lanex? Kayel frowned as he tried to shoot at the second creature, missed his target, and quickly reloaded his weapon.
Tenuk didn't react. He was too focused on his flight towards Nyssi and Thassalin, despite the other creature chasing them. Kayel awkwardly spun around to face the monster. The fact that it was chasing them was an advantage for Kayel, as it made it easier for him to aim and shoot. Two shots passed through the creature's upper wings, and it howled in pain before disappearing again beneath the trees. Kayel didn't know if it was still following them, but it was certainly not capable of catching up.
Further ahead, Nyssi was desperately clinging on, while Thassalin flew in circles, firing bursts of flame at the blackened monster. Although the creature was clearly wounded, it seemed furious and determined to keep fighting, and the fireballs didn't seem to have the desired effect. When Thassalin straightened up, Nyssi took the opportunity to draw her weapon, a reliable rifle. It was of course not intended for this kind of situation, but a volley of shots would surely at least discourage the black beast, wouldn't it?
